        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 23 at 9:50AM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 950 AM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles south of Mammoth Lakes, moving north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Thomas Edison and Volcanic Knob.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
